        <h2>Networking Expert</h2>

        <p>Dr. Lavian is a networking expert who provides consulting services in network communications, telecommunications, and internet protocols. He profoundly understands network communications, data communications, computer networks, and internet protocols, including TCP/IP, UDP, IP, MAC Ethernet, and IEEE 802.3.</p>

        <p>With his academic background and practical industry experience, Dr. Lavian comprehensively understands the relationships between network communications, computer networks, data communications, and wireless applications. He is highly skilled in designing, implementing, and architecture communications services in these fields. Dr. Lavian's expertise makes him a valuable resource for clients seeking expert consulting services in network communications.</p>

        <h3>Networking Expertise</h3>

        <p>Dr. Lavian is a networking expert who is proficient in network communications, computer networks, data communications, Internet protocols, and wireless applications. He profoundly understands the relationships between networking and communications applications. He is skilled in designing, implementing, and deploying networking systems and solutions. Dr. Lavian's expertise includes the following areas:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Computer networks, network architectures, network protocols, communication systems, communication devices, packet switching, networked systems, Internet technologies, distributed systems, and data center network architecture.</li>
          <li>Communication networks, Internet Protocols, TCP/IP Suite, TCP, UDP, IP, Ethernet, 802.3 Internet protocols.</li>
          <li>Network software, data link, network, transport, and application layers (L2, L3, L4, L7).</li>
          <li>Network security, load balancing, Firewalls, IPSec, VPN, and Tunneling.</li>
          <li>Network protocols, Broadband, ICMP, IGMP, ARP, ARQ, HARQ.</li>
          <li>LAN, WAN, VPN, Routing Protocols, RIP, BGP, MPLS, OSPF, Multicast, DNS, and DHCP.</li>
          <li>Bandwidth throttling, Quality of Service, QoS, Priority queuing, Classification, Provisioning, Packet Switching, and Switching.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Quality of Service (QoS) relates to routing, switching, and communications systems.</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Network Communication Architectures, Network Infrastructure, and Network Equipment.</li>
          <li>Network services include grid computing, cloud computing, content delivery networks, and distributed systems.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Core focus area as Networking Expert</h3>

        <p>The Internet is the basic technology of the Information Age; more than any other technology, networking, and communications have changed how we live, putting the Internet at our fingertips.</p>

        <p>The Networking and Communications areas focus on the architecture and design of data networks, communication systems, computer networks, and Web technologies. The Internet is the best example of interconnected computer networks that use the Internet protocol suite (TCP/IP) to communicate between many data networks, computer networks, and devices. Packet switching, used to group data transmitted over a digital network, is an integral part of this technology.</p>

        <p>As a networking expert, Dr. Lavian focuses on the architecture and design of data networks, communication systems, computer networks, and Web technologies. This includes a deep understanding of the Internet and how it works and the technologies that enable its functioning. Additionally, packet switching and its role in data transmission over digital networks form a core part of Dr. Lavian's focus areas.</p>

        <p>With a background in software development, network protocols, and communication technology products development, Dr. Lavian's interests and expertise encompass various aspects of networking and communications, including Broadband, DSL, Cable, LTE, 5G, WiFi, optical networking, multimedia streaming, VoIP, IoT, and more. His knowledge and experience in these areas enable him to assist companies and organizations in designing, implementing, and maintaining networks that cater to their specific needs and requirements.</p>

